which calls were placed will have to pay for the bills.
   A complete breakdown of the number of calls and where they were
placed was not available.
   About 4,300 police phones are electronically blocked from making
such calls; the calls were made on 2,700 that are unrestricted. A
three-month telephone company strike that ended last week has
hampered efforts to trace the calls.
   It was reported last month that two city school districts have
amassed more than $90,000 in calls to pay-per-call exchanges.
