sentenced to eight years in prison and fined $200,000.
   Dortch's plea agreement allowed him to remain free until he had
finished cooperating with the goverment. He testified against
Bakker at the former PTL leader's trial.
   Dortch had been scheduled to begin serving his sentence Oct. 13.
But on Oct. 5, his attorneys filed a motion asking that Dortch not
be required to report to prison until at least Jan. 15, ``so that
he might continue to comply with his agreement to cooperate with
the United States.''
   U.S. District Judge Robert Potter, who sentenced Bakker and
Dortch, granted the request.
