<FIRST>u a AM-Carter'sSister     11-30 0189</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Carter's Sister,0193</SECOND>
<HEAD>Carter's Sister Diagnosed With Same Cancer As Parents, Sister, Brother</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gloria Carter Spann, the last surviving sibling
of former President Jimmy Carter, has been diagnosed with
pancreatic cancer, the same disease that killed their father,
sister and brother and contributed to the death of their mother.
   Mrs. Spann, 62, is a patient at Emory University Hospital in
Atlanta, according to a statement from her doctor, released
Thursday by the Carter Presidential Center.
   The statement from Dr. Martin York said the cancer has spread to
Mrs. Spann's liver, but ``she is in excellent spirits and feels
quite well.''
   ``Options for treatment have been discussed with her, and she is
weighing the options,'' the statement said.
   Carter's brother, Billy, died of pancreatic cancer in September
1988 at age 51. His evangelist sister, Ruth Carter Stapleton,
succumbed to the disease at the age of 54 in September 1983.
Carter's father, James Earl Carter Sr., also died of the disease in
1953.
   Pancreatic cancer also was a contributing factor in the death of
Carter's mother, ``Miss Lillian'' Carter, who died in October 1983
at age 85.
</TEXT>
