<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Miss Manners' next bit of advice to her readers
might very well be not to leave one's mink coat in a chauffeured
limousine.
   Etiquette columnist Judith Martin, a.k.a. Miss Manners, did just
that with her $15,000 white mink and someone stole it while she was
inside a bookstore autographing copies of her latest book, ``Miss
Manners' Guide for the Turn of the Millenium.''
   ``The driver had stepped away for a minute and someone broke the
windows out,'' said police Officer H.L. Tucker. Other items,
including plane tickets, were also taken, with the total loss
valued at $19,000, police said.
