<FIRST>s w BC-DisabilitiesAct Adv03-1stAdd   11-30 0198</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Disabilities Act, Adv 03-1st Add,0201</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv03</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Sunday, Dec. 3, and thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>WASHN: Rudman says.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   The bill includes assorted timetables and exemptions:
   _Businesses with fewer than 25 employees are exempt from the
employment provisions for the first two years. After that, those
with fewer than 15 employees are exempt. Public accommodations
provisions take effect 18 months after enactment.
   _Smaller and shorter buildings are exempt from special elevator
requirements, but no exception is made for shopping malls or
medical offices.
   _All new public-transit vehicles must be accessible but those
already on the road need not be retrofitted.
   _Private bus companies would have six to seven years, depending
on their size, to begin buying new buses that are accessible to the
disabled. Since all buses last 10 to 12 years, the full conversion
of the fleet would be gradual.
   _Homosexuality, bisexuality, sexual behavior disorders are
excluded from the definition of disability, as are compulsive
gambling, pyromania, kleptomania and some other aberrations.
   _No punitive damages may be collected for violations. However,
fines of up to $50,000 for the first violation and $100,000 for
subsequent violations may be imposed under the accommodations
provision.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv for Sunday, Dec. 3</NOTE>
