<TEXT>
   Interest rate jitters continued to pressure the stock market
Wednesday, pushing prices lower. The Dow Jones average of 30
industrials fell 13.23 points to 2,688.78.
   The dollar turned in a mixed performance as the West German mark
continued to dominate the foreign-exchange markets. Gold prices
fell sharply in New York after edging higher overseas.
   Bond prices gave ground amid pessimism about the possibility
that interest rates will fall any time soon.
   Pork-belly futures fell the limit for the second straight day;
oil futures advanced; and grains and soybeans were mixed.
</TEXT>
