<HEAD>Uniroyal Goodrich To Sell Textile Unit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Uniroyal Goodrich Tire Co. said Thursday it
plans to sell part of its its textile operations to a joint venture
organized by Dominion Engineered Textile Inc. of Montreal, outside
investors and managers.
   Terms were not disclosed.
   The deal includes Uniroyal Goodrich plants in Hogansville, Ga.,
and Thomaston, Ga., which together employ 1,600 people. The plants
produce fabrics sold to makers of products such as conveyor belts
and tire hoses.
   Uniroyal Goodrich said it would continue to operate textile
facilities in Scottsville, Va., Winnsboro, S.C., and Lindsay,
Ontario. The plants supply Uniroyal Goodrich tire production
materials.
   Dominion Textile said the joint venture would acquire its
Canadian-based engineered fabrics division to create North
America's largest independent tire cord fabric maker.
