<FIRST>u f AM-USWest-Retirement     11-30 0155</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-US West-Retirement,0161</SECOND>
<HEAD>US West Offers Special Retirement Option to Managers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ENGLEWOOD, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   In an effort to reduce costs,
communications giant US West Inc. is offering special incentives to
about 20,000 managers to retire by next Feb. 28, company officials
announced Thursday.
   President Dick McCormick said he couldn't predict how many
managers might respond to the offer, but said about one-third of
eligible employees have accepted at other companies offering
similar programs.
   The program will enable 14,000 managers to qualify for pensions
five years sooner than under previous guidelines and add five years
of service for pension calculation purposes.
   Another 6,000 managers are eligible for immediate pensions
without the service-added provision because they already are at
least 45 years old and have 20 years of service.
   McCormick said retiring managers may choose a lump sum payment
in lieu of a service pension, and placement assistance and other
incentives also are being provided.
</TEXT>
